♪ I am the moral order ♪

31:15.370 --> 31:18.250
♪ The gleam of the blade
tempers feathers into a phantom Phoenix  ♪

31:18.340 --> 31:19.370
♪ And these Phoenix bones of mine ♪

31:19.450 --> 31:24.360
♪ Empower me
to pierce through the wind and waves ♪

31:25.700 --> 31:27.410
♪ Allow me ♪

31:27.430 --> 31:30.040
♪ To not linger in shame,
to not give way ♪

31:30.350 --> 31:32.900
♪ To not be faithless,
to not admit defeat ♪

31:33.290 --> 31:36.280
♪ A body of stubborn pride
rises to shout that I ♪

31:36.320 --> 31:38.890
♪ Was never a creature
meant for the shallows ♪

31:39.230 --> 31:40.430
♪ Allow me ♪

31:40.620 --> 31:42.010
♪ To never pause ♪

31:42.360 --> 31:43.360
♪ Allow me ♪

31:43.760 --> 31:45.050
♪ To dare to shatter my bones ♪

31:45.250 --> 31:53.150
♪ Wherever I stand,
I dare to write a legend of glory ♪

31:46.550 --> 31:50.920
Long live the Emperor!

31:51.400 --> 31:55.640
Long live the Empress!

32:09.200 --> 32:10.000
What's wrong?

32:10.310 --> 32:11.370
Why are you sighing

32:12.350 --> 32:13.210
out of the blue?

32:13.830 --> 32:14.760
Are you unhappy?

32:15.720 --> 32:16.940
I'm not unhappy.

32:17.880 --> 32:18.830
I just feel...

32:19.830 --> 32:21.230
all of this feels unreal.

32:22.550 --> 32:23.880
It's because all of this

32:24.160 --> 32:25.690
is happening inside a book?

32:28.270 --> 32:29.130
I was thinking,

32:30.160 --> 32:31.760
when you entered this world,

32:32.120 --> 32:33.780
it was already on 'hell mode'.

32:34.510 --> 32:36.640
You were forced to fight for survival.

32:37.480 --> 32:38.920
As your only peer,

32:39.680 --> 32:41.340
I naturally became your ally.

32:42.200 --> 32:43.260
Us coming together

32:44.160 --> 32:45.640
seems inevitable.

32:47.640 --> 32:49.770
I know it's pointless to dwell on this,

32:50.680 --> 32:52.810
but sometimes I can't help but wonder,

32:54.000 --> 32:55.720
what if we weren't in this book?

32:55.720 --> 32:57.180
If we weren't in this book,

32:58.200 --> 32:59.350
by 2026,

33:01.150 --> 33:03.410
I would have been working for a few years.

33:04.750 --> 33:07.010
We probably would have met on the subway.

33:08.160 --> 33:08.730
What?

33:11.440 --> 33:12.500
After work one day,

33:13.810 --> 33:16.050
I was scrolling through my phone
on the subway.

33:16.050 --> 33:17.050
Suddenly, I heard

33:17.640 --> 33:19.700
someone next to me laughing out loud.

33:20.720 --> 33:21.580
I looked up,

33:22.680 --> 33:24.480
and saw she was also on her phone.

33:24.830 --> 33:25.960
I took a closer look,

33:27.400 --> 33:29.200
and realized she was quite cute.

33:31.710 --> 33:34.110
She definitely doesn't like being watched.

33:34.110 --> 33:34.830
Maybe...

33:35.350 --> 33:37.210
she'd even look up to glare at you,

33:37.750 --> 33:38.680
only to realize,

33:39.160 --> 33:40.560
it's a good-looking guy.

33:41.000 --> 33:41.830
So...

33:42.350 --> 33:43.950
she'd secretly forgive you.

33:45.750 --> 33:47.860
Then I'd push my luck.

33:49.000 --> 33:50.260
I'd ask for her number.

33:50.790 --> 33:52.050
Would she give it to me?

33:53.860 --> 33:54.920
That's hard to say.

33:57.200 --> 33:58.310
Then I would...

34:03.960 --> 34:05.020
What are you doing?

34:05.760 --> 34:06.500
Please?

34:07.270 --> 34:08.429
I'm not a weirdo.

34:09.510 --> 34:10.510
Just give it to me.

34:11.409 --> 34:12.219
Okay, okay.

34:13.800 --> 34:14.320
Great!

34:15.150 --> 34:15.800
Great!

34:18.440 --> 34:20.980
Then I'd start talking to her
about novels,

34:21.030 --> 34:22.429
and ask her to the movies.

34:22.440 --> 34:23.270
And then,

34:23.400 --> 34:24.280
we'd eat at

34:24.360 --> 34:26.420
the top ten hotpot places in the city.

34:27.920 --> 34:28.949
Our relationship

34:29.190 --> 34:31.719
would grow more in sync
with each passing day.

34:34.670 --> 34:35.550
After that,

34:37.000 --> 34:38.960
I'd send her flowers every day.

34:40.320 --> 34:41.380
Bunch after bunch.

34:42.960 --> 34:44.480
I'd send lots of flowers.

34:54.920 --> 34:56.179
How long can I hold out?

34:58.150 --> 34:58.950
Three months?

35:00.710 --> 35:01.440
Four months?

35:03.150 --> 35:03.960
Or half a year?

35:06.070 --> 35:07.480
On the way home one day,

35:08.480 --> 35:11.080
as I clutched the ring box tightly
in my pocket,

35:11.440 --> 35:12.170
I'd tell her,

35:14.070 --> 35:15.230
I can't imagine

35:16.550 --> 35:18.280
the rest of my life without you.

35:22.150 --> 35:24.280
Then I'd secretly watch her reaction.

35:26.840 --> 35:28.170
If she doesn't respond,

35:28.920 --> 35:29.650
then I'll...

35:30.630 --> 35:31.840
just wait a bit longer.

35:31.840 --> 35:32.570
Impossible.

35:33.230 --> 35:34.890
Are you that timid of a person?

35:35.960 --> 35:36.760
I was afraid she wouldn't agree.

35:36.340 --> 35:38.500
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

35:38.840 --> 35:40.090
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

35:40.420 --> 35:42.560
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

35:42.940 --> 35:44.260
♪ Drinking alone, hard to get drunk ♪

35:43.440 --> 35:44.400
But over here...

35:44.350 --> 35:46.720
♪ Words unspoken ♪

35:45.320 --> 35:46.450
there are no subways

35:47.000 --> 35:47.710
or movies.

35:48.280 --> 35:50.760
♪ Shyness unhidden ♪

35:52.410 --> 35:54.590
♪ Walking down a street together ♪

35:53.920 --> 35:54.450
Who says?

35:54.770 --> 35:55.940
♪ Shoulder to shoulder ♪

35:56.350 --> 35:58.390
♪ Raising my head, lowering my eyes ♪

35:56.670 --> 35:57.270
Follow me.

35:58.770 --> 36:00.250
♪ Blushing slightly ♪

36:00.360 --> 36:02.780
♪ A face flushed red at first sight ♪

36:04.350 --> 36:07.590
♪ A smile like a flower in my heart ♪

36:08.250 --> 36:11.660
♪ Whose longing lingers day and night? ♪

36:12.330 --> 36:15.390
♪ Piling up stories
and countless thoughts ♪

36:15.830 --> 36:17.660
♪ Walking through once, taking a glance ♪

36:17.880 --> 36:19.540
♪ All lingering and wandering ♪

36:19.820 --> 36:21.510
♪ How many rains, how many winds? ♪

36:21.770 --> 36:23.920
♪ Looking back, it's all like smoke ♪

36:24.370 --> 36:27.520
♪ Watching the hazy world ♪

36:28.360 --> 36:30.700
♪ Who still guards that yearning? ♪

36:30.820 --> 36:31.920
♪ Still unchanged ♪

36:32.360 --> 36:35.210
♪ Even if months and years
pass in a blink ♪

36:35.850 --> 36:37.310
♪ One thought for a lifetime ♪

36:37.430 --> 36:41.560
♪ Waiting for someone to appear ♪

36:37.670 --> 36:38.230
Empress.

36:39.370 --> 36:40.900
I'll show you a magic trick.

36:58.370 --> 37:00.530
♪ A letter, a line of words ♪

36:59.110 --> 36:59.640
Look!

37:00.870 --> 37:02.070
♪ Picking up the pen again and again ♪

37:02.420 --> 37:04.510
♪ A cup of tea, a glass of wine ♪

37:04.930 --> 37:06.280
